cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with data mining on Call Data Records (CDR) to identify user habits and draw their characterizing profiles. This falls under the domain of data management and analysis, which is covered by the cs.DB sub-category. The paper also employs unsupervised clustering techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining, and thus it could also be classified under cs.SI (Statistical Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with generating additional fields to describe implicit information hidden in data, which could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
